<br>
My guild is a mid-tier guild on the 7th Hammer server.  We are currently killing dragons for ST keys (we have 12 so far), farming HoT some for armor (mostly done with this) and still killing Vindi and Velks for drops as well.  We have also killed Xanamech about 10 times in PoI and a couple SoL boss mobs too.  We are not yet doing NToV, Ssra, or VT.<br>
<br>
I am the MA for our guild, they have me tank about 80% of all our raids, but nothing is ever defaulted to me.  I have to roll against everyone else on drops.  For example, we have killed Xanamech 10 times and have had the 41% haste neck drop 4 times and I have yet to win one.  I'm a 65 warrior still using an RBB, yet one of our 61 warriors with only 3k hp unbuffed has the haste neck <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I'm just curious what your guilds do.  My guild refuses to do points, and there is a huge amount of resistance against defaulting anything to anyone.  Am I being selfish to suggest that I get dibs on items since I am the MA tank for nearly all of our raids?  Sometimes I feel like I do all the work and other people are getting my paycheck, lol -- it's painful when I am asked to tank every time we do a raid, yet I watch everyone else in the guild get the upgrades (I have the WORST luck on rolls, so I never win much). <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=193463"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://webpages.charter.net/mtiffan/Scargoth_logo_2.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:orange;font-family:century gothic;">65 Ogre Overlord</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.savagearms.org" target="top"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:yellow;font-family:century gothic;">Savage Arms Guild</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=farlanderb>FarlanderB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 110<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/25/03 8:04 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How does your guild equip the MA warrior?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Disclaimer: I do not mean this as a flame! I am answering the question.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Personally, I do think that asking for dibs is selfish. I believe that merrit works best for guilds looking to move on to bigger and better things. I do not believe in giving the best gear to the MA first since he takes all the hits. Like you said, you are there 80% of the time... but what about that other 20% when the guild needs a good tank too? Many guilds expect to see their members progress in levels and AA points as well, where they also need gear. I personally feel that merrit should be equal distribution with some, but not much, emphasis put on role on most of the raids.<br>
<br>
However, I would agree that you should have recieved one of those haste neck pieces because you do do most of the tanking and you still didn't have one. But I do not agree that you get first dibs on ALL items.<br>
<br>
And if you are not having fun just tanking the mob, I would suggest you try a different class where you'll have more fun. Don't play this game if you aren't having fun anymore.. this is a break FROM work, not more of it.<br>
<br>
